  "instruction": "I need to inspect a JTAG TAP-controller waveform in GTKWave. Open /home/user/Desktop/jtag.vcd, then add the following signals to the Signals pane in this exact order — from scope `tb`: `treset`, `tck`, `tms`, `jtagState[3:0]`; from scope `tb.u0`: `J_state_ascii[111:0]`. Right-click `J_state_ascii` and set its Data Format to ASCII so the state names (`testLogicReset`, `runTest`, `shiftDR`, …) become readable, and set `jtagState`'s Data Format to Decimal. Zoom to fit. Then visually scan `J_state_ascii` to find the first time the state enters `shiftDR` and drop a named marker called `firstShiftDR` at that timestamp (Markers → Drop Named Marker). Finally save the session via File → Write Save File As… to /home/user/Desktop/jtag.gtkw.",
